-- ECB funding to Greek banks falls in June
-- 
-- Tue Jul 15, 2014 10:30AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, July 15 (Reuters) - European Central Bank (ECB) funding to Greek banks fell in June by 5.71 billion euros, Bank of Greece data showed on Tuesday. The funding dropped to 44.95 billion euros ($61.1 billion) from 50.66 billion euros in May.   (Reporting by Harry Papachristou and George Georgiopoulos)  ((harry.Papachristou@thomsonreuters.com; +30 210 33 76 455; Reuters Messaging: harry.papachristou@thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))

